===Personal income=== The average median household income of the cities was $35,946 (rounded to nearest dollar) - 25.90% less than the state average ($48,508). Only one city (South Burlington) exceeds the national average household income.
===Area=== The aggregate area of Vermont's cities totaled {{convert|80.2|sqmi|km2|abbr=on}}.{{Citation needed|date=February 2011}} This is approximately 0.8% of the total area of {{convert|9,620|sqmi|km2|abbr=on}}.{{Citation needed|reason=this is an WP:OR observation unless you can find WP:RELY source pointing it out. Otherwise we would have Wikipedia editors doing ALL the research and writing|date=February 2011}}
